"    Compared to native vessel stenting, the probability of requiring any revascularization (upper panel) or revascularization of non-target sites (non-TSR, middle panel) is higher for saphenous vein graft stenting. However, the probability of revascularization of a target site is similar for stents placed in native vessels and saphenous grafts (lower panel).",
